id="how-to-make-a-logo-in-illustrator-section3" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>3.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=using-shapes>Using shapes.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-make-a-logo-in-illustrator-section3-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=pick-a-shape-for-your-logo>Pick a shape for your logo.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-pick-a-shape-for-your-logo-288x288-2021093.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Pick a shape for your logo."></div></div><p>The shape will become the structure of the logo and contain the icon. Different shapes have various associations and can be used to communicate certain values and characteristics of your business.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-make-a-logo-in-illustrator-section3-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=select-the-shape-tool>Select the Shape Tool.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-select-the-shape-tool-288x288-2021093.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Select the Shape Tool."></div></div><p>You'll find the "Shape Tool" in the left menu bar. Right-click on the icon to select the type of shape. In this case, we're using the "Rectangle Tool (M)."</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-make-a-logo-in-illustrator-section3-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
