ect","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-change-the-text-color-288x288-2021093.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Set the \"Stroke\" color to \"[None].\"<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"3","name":"<p>Change the font.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Adjust the look of your text by selecting a font from the drop-down menu. You'll find this in the middle of the top menu bar.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/guides/how-to-make-a-logo-in-illustrator#how-to-make-a-logo-in-illustrator-section9-step3","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-change-the-font-288x288-2021093.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Position your text by selecting the \"Selection Tool (V)\" and dragging your text box into place.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>You can adjust the text style, size, leading, kerning, and tracking parameters by clicking on \"Character\" in the top menu bar.<\/p>\n"}]}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"10","name":"<p>Creating variations of your logo.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Compare different styles of your design.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Once you've completed the general structure of your logo, you can start to play with the details.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/guides/how-to-make-a-logo-in-illustrator#how-to-make-a-logo-in-illustrator-section10-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-compare-different-styles-of-your-design-288x288-2021091.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>Try different background colors, shape outlines, fonts, and arrangements to refine the look of your logo.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>This will help you picture what your logo will look like in different contexts and help you make a decision.<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Create Artboards.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Click on the \"Artboards Tool (Shift + O)\" icon on the left menu bar and ensure that the \"Move\/Copy Artwork with Artboard\" option is selected in the top menu bar. Then, hold \"Alt\" on Windows or \"Option\" on Mac and click and drag the canvas to create a copy of the logo on a new Artboard.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/guides/how-to-make-a-logo-in-illustrator#how-to-make-a-logo-in-illustrator-section10-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-create-artboards-288x288-2022015.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>Repeat the process to create additional Artboards.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Experiment with colors, outlines, and compositional layouts to compare different versions of your design and help inform your final decision.<\/p>\n"}]}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"11","name":"<p>Finishing up.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Export your logo.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Once you're happy with your logo design, you can export it in various file formats.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/guides/how-to-make-a-logo-in-illustrator#how-to-make-a-logo-in-illustrator-section11-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-export-your-logo-288x288-2021093.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Click on \"File\" in the main menu bar, hover over \"Export,\" and select \"Export As...\"<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Specify the export destination on your computer.<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Select a file format.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>The benefit of Illustrator is that it creates vector files, which offer infinite resolution and can therefore scale perfectly for various applications. When you save an Illustrator project, it will save it as an \"AI\" document. This is also known as a \"Working,\" \"Source,\" or \"Master\" file that contains your workspace where edits can be made.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/guides/how-to-make-a-logo-in-illustrator#how-to-make-a-logo-in-illustrator-section11-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-select-a-file-format-288x288-2021093.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>The pop-up window will show your different export options.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Choose a file type from the drop-down menu of the \"Format\" tab.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>\"EPS\" and \"SVG\" formats are vector files that allow you to scale the images without quality loss. They are designed for print and web, respectively.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>\"PNG\" and \"JPG\" files are pixel-based and will lose resolution when scaled up. The former allows for transparent backgrounds, while the latter does not.<\/p>\n"}]}]}]}</script> <div
